               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340220-182-person1718">
                  MARY 
                  FINLEY
               <interp inst="t18340220-182-person1718" type="surname" value="FINLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340220-182-person1718" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340220-182-person1718" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I <rs id="t18340220-182-viclabel1038" type="occupation">keep a haberdasher's shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340220-182-victim1717 t18340220-182-viclabel1038"></join> in <placeName id="t18340220-182-crimeloc1039">Stepney</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18340220-182-crimeloc1039" type="placeName" value="Stepney"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18340220-182-crimeloc1039" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340220-182-off1036 t18340220-182-crimeloc1039"></join>- on the 8th of February, at half-past two o'clock, the prisoner came into my shop and asked to look at some silk handkerchiefs - I showed her one out of the window - she said it was too thin - I then turned some out of a box - a man came in without shoes, begging - I said I had nothing to give him - he snatched the handkerchief, which I was showing to the prisoner, and ran away - I had seen him standing on the left of the window when the prisoner came in - I ran to the door and cried "Stop thief!" but not knowing which way the man run, I returned to the shop, recollecting that I had left the handkerchiefs on the counter - I then pushed the prisoner to the door, but Mrs. Freeman called to me to detain her, as she belonged to the man - I then told her, if she would tell me where the man was, that I might get the handkerchief, she might go - but she would not.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340220-182-person1719">
                  SARAH 
                  FREEMAN
               <interp inst="t18340220-182-person1719" type="surname" value="FREEMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340220-182-person1719" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340220-182-person1719" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live opposite Mrs. Finley - I was standing at my window about half-past two o'clock, and saw the prisoner come up the street, and stop at the window - a young man was with her without shoes and stockings - they were conversing together, and stopped at her window - they were talking together - the prisoner went into the shop - the young man waited by the window - I saw Mrs. Finley show the prisoner some handkerchiefs, and the man went in and snatched the handkerchief, and came out - I saw it was a red handkerchief - he folded it up and put it in his bosom - I had seen them about three minutes, and looking in at the window.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340220-182-person1720">
                  JOHN 
                  JAMES
               <interp inst="t18340220-182-person1720" type="surname" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340220-182-person1720" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340220-182-person1720" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (police-constable, K 256.) I took the prisoner - she had no money on her, nothing but a small knife - I took her about twenty minutes before three o'clock.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340220-182-person1721">
                  JOHN 
                  ROBERTSON
               <interp inst="t18340220-182-person1721" type="surname" value="ROBERTSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340220-182-person1721" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340220-182-person1721" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was a constable - I have a certificate<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183402200104"></xptr>of the prisoner's former conviction, which I got at Mr. Clark's office - I know her to be the person (read).</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was going up the street, a young man came and asked me to go and look at a handkerchief for him - I said, "Yes, if you give me the money"- we went on, there was one in the window - he said, "I want a deeper red one" - I went in and asked for it - he came in and stole it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18340220-182-verdict1040" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18340220-182-verdict1040" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 18. - <rs id="t18340220-182-punish1041" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18340220-182-punish1041" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340220-182-defend1715 t18340220-182-punish1041"></join>
               Transported for Seven Years
            </rs>.</p>
